snippet.textDisplay: This dude is awesome as hell. Also, I am much more a auditory based person when making music myself, so in that place, I'd likely slip right into do that while there learning. I think it'd pick up each thing really quick. It's like a puzzle to me, and whatever I identify sounding the best to me, is usually what I will then stick to in order to build off of, onto and from. Also as a fun fact about records, again, most records are one song, and they were and still are referred to as "LPs", which is an acronym for "Long Plays", while there were some others that had two songs on them, one per side, and they were & are called "EPs", or, "Extended Plays".
